50|$|Rabbi Hershel Reichman, has {{authored}} seven {{volumes of}} Reshimos Shiurim which are lucid notes and explanations of Rabbi Soloveitchik's lectures on specific {{sections of the}} Talmud. These include the Mesechtot ("Tractates") of Sukkah, <b>Shevuot,</b> Nedarim, Bava Kamma, Berachot and Yevamot. The Rav gave shiur for one year on the particularly challenging tractate of Yevamot {{in the year of}} 1962-63. Additionally, Rav Reichman is a teacher of Hasidism, and is particularly fond of the philosophy of the Shem Mishmuel.|$|R
