5000|$|Joshua ben Levi (Yehoshua ben Levi) was an amora, {{a scholar}} of the Talmud, {{who lived in the}} Land of Israel {{in the first half of}} the third century. He lived and taught in the city of Lod. Rabbi Yehoshua was an elder {{contemporary}} of Johanan bar Nappaha and Resh Lakish, who presided over the school in Tiberias. (Genesis Rabbah 94.) With Johanan bar Nappaha, he often engaged in homiletic exegetical discussions (Babylonian Talmud Bava Batra 116a; Megillah 27a; <b>Shevuot</b> 18b).|$|R
